<br />

<br />
No...if a mob is a paladin/shadowknight, it will never dual weild.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">5. When I charm stuff in ldon, i notice my pet has crap regen ability, would giving it an iksar regen bp make a huge difference in getting my pet up to snuff. Does anyone have any tricks for getting the pet battle ready again?? </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
You could break charm...mezz...mem blur.  Since mob is non-aggro, it will regen to full hp in a few ticks.  This is a pain in the ass...just get your healer to throw it a good heal.  Other than that...no.  Giving it a regen item is probably prohibitively expensive and of very little effect to a mob with at least 12k hp.  NDT/Boon would provide many more HP than trying to give your pet a regen item.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
