                        <tr>
                                <td width="100%"><a href="viewtopic.php?p=15344&amp;sid=a98deff80f96321a53d1dd5adcfd8a30#15344"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails">Posted: Wed Dec 31, 2003 1:10 pm<span class="gen">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; &nbsp;Post subject: Re: 3-4 dirge charm questions</span></td>
                                <td valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><a href="posting.php?mode=quote&amp;p=15344&amp;sid=a98deff80f96321a53d1dd5adcfd8a30"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/lang_english/icon_quote.gif" alt="Reply with quote" title="Reply with quote" border="0" /></a>    </td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">1. If I give a ssoy and a mithril 2-hander, will they use both?
<br />

<br />
No, pets follow the same general rules as players, if the pet decides to use the mith two hander, then it can't wield anything else.
<br />

<br />
2. Will a box knight or crusader (knight classes i assume) use 2 1handers?
<br />

<br />
From time to time you'll run across creatures that won't duel wield no matter what you give them, but this seems to be related to some flag other than their class.  For example, wurms in burning woods will duel wield if given two daggers, but monkey men in maidens eye won't.  In general just dire charm the bugger and give it two different 1H weapons and see if it works or not.  I don't know if this has been fixed or not but for dire charm pets, if you give the pet two of the exact same weapon, one will get destroyed.  Something about monsters cannot store two of the exact same item.
<br />

<br />
3. I don't like to get overburdened with loot, especially the weap drops, can i give item drops such as pages or gems to my pet, and when i kill it at end o' nite for reclaim weaps, get back my loot...using it as a type of 'mule' for the eve?
<br />

<br />
No, there is something about monsters only holding 1 of an item, maybe a bug or something.  Its been a while since I dire charmed, maybe this has been fixed.  
<br />

<br />
4. Follow up on the mithril 2-hander...Great haste, but is a 2 hander a good thing to go over with a creature over 2 decent 1 handers?
<br />

<br />
Go with 2 1H weapons, and don't worry about splurging, a rusty dagger does just as well as a fine steel dagger, and your enchanter haste will be plenty.  Remember, the DC pet will be hitting for some pretty insane amounts of damage, any tiny extra amount of damage you manage to squeeze out of the pet with expensive pet weapons isn't really going to be noticeable.  One exception you might consider are gnoll hide lariets that proc a stun, those could be useful in certain situations, but I've found I have to get a shammy to buff the pets dex to get the pet to proc a lot.
<br />

<br />
5. When I charm stuff in ldon, i notice my pet has crap regen ability, would giving it an iksar regen bp make a huge difference in getting my pet up to snuff.  Does anyone have any tricks for getting the pet battle ready again??
<br />

<br />
These is the obvious break charm / mem blur method, another thing you can do is tell the pet to /guard, then put some distance between you and the pet and then invis yourself.  If you have enough distance between you and the pet, it will instantly heal itself.  I'm kind of guessing from the context of this question that your trying to do ldon dungeons solo or grouped with non healers.  If thats the case, it can be effective to dispel the pet (dispels haste), then stun, then root, then pacify (or not) then mem blur until the pet heals itself.
<br />

<br />
6. Last, and silliest of the questions...would a mage dmg bracer help increase the amt. of proc damage a yak club or whatnot proc?
<br />

<br />
I would guess not, but I don't have any empirical evidence to support that guess.  In general, just dire charm the bugger, give it some 1h weapons (two different ones), haste it and let the good times roll.  Don't fret to much about nuances and such.
<br />

<br />
- Pahbi</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
