                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Would like to add my comments and experiences with DC for what they are worth. My personal favourite zone for DC is Veksar , by some way. It appears that mob regen is much faster here than in any other zone, and the pets can melee for a couple of fights,then regen in just a few minutes.
<br />
My method is to mix melee with nukes, and use rune on myself to tank the mob for a while to allow pet to regen/lifetap with NDT. This allows almost constant pulling, and I have made a BUNCH of AA in this zone. 
<br />

<br />
All the early camps are soloable, up to and including shop. The deeper areas are trickier, when you jump out of shop window, the pet takes a weird path, and can aggro a little train of his own on the way ! (Maybe someone knows a safer way to get to Highborn area?)
<br />
I am happy with either a crusader or sentry as a pet, crusader HT's every now and again, but wastes a little time casting spells. Both will dual wield, but not with some weapons. just keep giving them other types of weapon until they dual wield ! 
<br />

<br />
The other place for fun DC'ing I have found is the Enforcer area in PoJ. DC a rat in the nearby corridors, equip,haste, NDT, and head to enforcers. With a little luck, the whole room can be kept clear, but just do as many of them as is comfortable. The mobs come in pairs, so we need to Pacify one and pull the one opposite. Nice AA exp and very nice pp to be had here <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
There are other zones where DC works well, Seb is fun, but not much exp there at 65. Chardok will give a nice 135-140 hitting pet, but much more downtime there in my experience.
<br />
Soloing with DC in PoP is barely possible, and not really worth the effort. I just use DC in a group to hike up the DPS nicely.
<br />
Just a few of my observations...and imo, DC is absolutely the BEST AA we get.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
